Dale-Chall Word List Provenance
================================

Source: Dale, Edgar; Chall, Jeanne S. "Readability Revisited: The New
Dale-Chall Readability Formula." Brookline Books, 1995.

Original: Dale, Edgar; Chall, Jeanne S. "A Formula for Predicting
Readability." Educational Research Bulletin, Vol. 27, 1948.

The Dale-Chall 3000-word list has been widely reproduced in educational
research, textbooks, and open-source readability tools. The word list
consists of common English words familiar to at least 80% of 4th-grade
students, as determined by reading comprehension surveys.

This word list is compiled from multiple publicly available sources in
the educational research domain. It is used here for computational
readability analysis purposes.
